{"questionId":"1931121","questionHtml":"<p>The Hertzsprung–Russell diagram shows two stars,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>X</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Y</mtext></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/bfdf8322d23a08df4871e0727b6b59b716b36fc9.png\"></p>\n<p>What is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>radius</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>of</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>radius</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>of</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; 4</p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; 16</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"1931121","referenceCode":"SPM.1A.SL.TZ0.25","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"The Hertzsprung–Russell diagram shows two stars, X and Y. What is radius of Xradius of Y? A. 116 B. 14 C. 4 D. 16","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"25","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["E. Nuclear and quantum physics","E. Nuclear and quantum physics","E.5 Fusion and stars"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}